  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.",
    "Add diced onion and sauté until translucent, about 5 minutes.",
    "Stir in minced garlic and smoked paprika, cooking for 1 minute until fragrant.",
    "Mix in tomato paste and cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.",
    "Pour in crushed canned tomatoes and chopped confit tomatoes, stirring to combine.",
    "Add lemon zest, lemon juice, dried thyme, and bay leaf, then season with salt and pepper.",
    "Bring the mixture to a gentle simmer, cover, and let cook for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Remove the bay leaf, taste and adjust seasoning if needed.",
    "Ladle the stew into bowls and sprinkle chopped parsley on top.",
    "Serve hot with crusty bread or over cooked rice."
  ],
